@startuml async-callback-delivery
' How an async payload reaches callbackUrl, and the three outcome buckets.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/api/async-responses.md
!include _style.puml
skinparam wrapWidth 260

start
:payload ready
(the agent's response, or an error
envelope such as delivery_failed
or wake_timeout);

if (spec.webhook.callbackUrl set?) then (yes)

  :**pre-dial re-check**
  re-resolve the callbackUrl host against
  the deny ranges and the configured
  gateway.callbackUrl.allowlist
  (defeats DNS rebinding since
  reconcile-time validation);

  if (host still passes?) then (yes)

    repeat
      :sign per spec.webhook.callbackAuth
      (bearer, or HMAC over requestId,
      timestamp, sha256(body))
      **fresh timestamp every attempt**;
      :POST to the **pinned IP:port**
      (hostname kept for Host and TLS SNI);

      if (attempt outcome?) then (delivered: 2xx)
        :**DELIVERED**
        receiver has the payload
        nothing is stored for polling;
        stop
      elseif (**TERMINAL**\n401, 403, 404,\n405, 410, 415) then
        :no retry
        Warning event
        reason=CallbackRejected; <<#FFE4B5>>
        break
      else (**RETRIED**\nconnect error, TLS failure,\nread timeout (10s),\n408, 429, 422, 5xx)
      endif
    repeat while (attempts < 4?) is (yes: back off 1s, 5s, 25s) not (no: budget exhausted)

  else (no)
    :**BYPASSED: callback_invalid**
    no retry, and no fresh
    callback_invalid envelope
    Warning event
    reason=CallbackInvalid; <<#FFE4B5>>
  endif

else (no)
  :no callback target; <<#F5F5F5>>
endif

:**Patch** the payload into
agentry-async-{requestId};

if (Patch lands within its own\n1s/5s/25s, 4-attempt budget?) then (yes)
  :polls return **200** until the
  1h-from-202-acceptance TTL;
  stop
else (no)
  :payload dropped silently
  agentry_channel_async_patch_failed_total
  pollers see **202** until
  the TTL flips to **404**; <<#FFCDD2>>
  stop
endif

legend bottom
  **Three buckets, three behaviors.** RETRIED and TERMINAL both end at the
  polling store; they differ only in whether the retry budget is spent first.
  BYPASSED is the odd one: callback_invalid is **not** the stored error.type.
  The URL is rejected before dial, so there is nothing to sign and nothing to
  POST, and the **underlying** payload (the agent's response, or the
  delivery_failed / wake_timeout envelope) is what reaches polling instead.
endlegend

@enduml
